<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/jcrop/dist/jcrop.css">
<script src="https://unpkg.com/jcrop"></script>


<div data-bind="hidden: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.octoprint_nanny.auth_valid" >

    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span-6">
            <img class="img-fluid" src="plugin/octoprint_nanny/static/img/logo-square-excited.png"/>
        </div>

        <h3>You haven't authenticated yet!</h3>

        <p>To get started, open OctoPrint's <i class="fa fa-wrench"></i> settings menu and save your Print Nanny auth token. </p>
        <p>
        Looking for help? <a href="https://github.com/bitsy-ai/octoprint-nanny-plugin/issues/new/choose">Create a Github issue</a> to report a bug or get support.
        
        </p>
        <p>
            <a href="https://discord.gg/YK7qnv5KjB">Join the Discord server</a> to chat, share your projects, and let us know what you think of Print Nanny.

        </p>
    </div>


</div>

<div data-bind="visible: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.octoprint_nanny.auth_valid() && !settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.octoprint_nanny.device_registered()" >

    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span-6">
            <img class="img-fluid" src="plugin/octoprint_nanny/static/img/logo-square-excited.png"/>
        </div>

        <h3>Your device is not registered yet!</h3>

        <p>To get started, open OctoPrint's <i class="fa fa-wrench"></i> settings menu and register your device.</p>
        <p>
        Looking for help? <a href="https://github.com/bitsy-ai/octoprint-nanny-plugin/issues/new/choose">Create a Github issue</a> to report a bug or get support.
        
        </p>
        <p>
            <a href="https://discord.gg/YK7qnv5KjB">Join the Discord server</a> to chat, share your projects, and let us know what you think of Print Nanny.
        </p>
    </div>


</div>

<div data-bind="visible: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.octoprint_nanny.auth_valid() && settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.octoprint_nanny.device_registered()" >
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <h2>Print Nanny Status</h2>
        <p>
        Looking for help? <a href="https://github.com/bitsy-ai/octoprint-nanny-plugin/issues/new/choose">Create a Github issue</a> to report a bug or ask a question.
        </p>
        <p>
            <a href="https://discord.gg/YK7qnv5KjB">Join the Discord server</a> to share your projects and hang out with cool people. ðŸ˜Ž
        </p>
        <p><a href="https://www.print-nanny.com/health/" target="_blank">Print Nanny system status</a></p>
            <table class="table">
            <thead>
            <tr>
            <th>Connection Name</th>
            <th>Status</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <tr>
            <td data-bind="class: apiStatusClass">{{ plugin_octoprint_nanny_settings.api_url }} </td>
            <td>
                <span data-bind="text: apiStatusMessage"></span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
            <tr>
            <td data-bind="class: mqttPingStatusClass">{{ plugin_octoprint_nanny_settings.mqtt_bridge_hostname }}:{{ plugin_octoprint_nanny_settings.mqtt_bridge_port }} (ping)</td>
            <td><span data-bind="text: mqttPingStatusMessage"></span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
            <td data-bind="class: mqttPongStatusClass">{{ plugin_octoprint_nanny_settings.mqtt_bridge_hostname }}:{{ plugin_octoprint_nanny_settings.mqtt_bridge_port }} (pong)</td>
            <td><span data-bind="text: mqttPongStatusMessage"></span></td>
            </tr>
            </tbody>
            </table>
            <button data-bind="{click: testConnectionsAsync }" type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">
                Test Connections
            </button>
        <hr/>

        <h2>Print Nanny Monitoring</h2>
            <div class="alert alert-block" data-bind="hidden: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.octoprint_nanny.webcam_to_octoprint_ws">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="alert">&times;</button>
            
                <h4 class="alert-heading">OctoPrint Streaming Disabled</h4> 
                <p>Check out the stream in Print Nanny's UI instead: https://www.print-nanny.com/dashboard</p>
                <p>You can re-enable this in Print Nanny's advanced settings menu by checking the "Show webcam stream in OctoPrint UI" option.</p>
            </div>
        <div data-bind="visible: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.octoprint_nanny.webcam_to_octoprint_ws" >
            <p>Sending notifications to: <strong><span data-bind="text: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.octoprint_nanny.user_email"></span></strong>
            </p>
            <hr/>
            <img id="tab_plugin_octoprint_nanny_preview" data-bind="attr: { src: imageData }"/>

            <hr/>

            <div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert" data-bind="visible: settingsViewModel.settings.plugins.octoprint_nanny.calibrated() == false">
            <h4 class="alert-heading">Warning! Calibration Required</h4>
            <p>Click the <strong>Start</strong> button below, then click the <strong>Calibrate</strong> button to get started.</p>
            </div>

            <button data-bind="{click: startMonitoring }" type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">
                Start Monitoring
            </button>

            <button data-bind="{click: stopMonitoring, enable: previewActive }" type="submit" class="btn btn-danger btn-large">
                Stop Monitoring
            </button>

            <button data-bind="{click: calibrate, enable: previewActive() && !calibrationActive() }" type="submit" class="btn btn-warning btn-large">
                Show Calibration
            </button>
        </div>

    </div>
    <div data-bind="{visible: calibrationActive}">
        <h3>Calibrate Area of Interest</h3>
        <p>Right-click the image below, then draw a loose box around your printer's XYZ area.</p> 
        
        <p>
        <button class="btn btn-primary" type="submit" data-bind="{click: saveCalibration, enable: calibratePos }">
            Save Calibration
        </button>

        <button class="btn btn-secondary btn-small" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseExample" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseExample">
            Show Example
        </button>
        </p>
        <div class="collapse" id="collapseExample">
            <p>In this example, Print Nanny detects the Prusa's LCD case is a 3D-printed object. While the case <i>technically</i> is a 3D print</i>, monitoring a completed print would be silly!</p>
            
            <p>Select your print volume's approximate area to exclude objects outside of the print bed. </p>
            
            <img src="plugin/octoprint_nanny/static/img/ignore_mask_example.gif"/>
        </div>

        <div id="tab_plugin_octoprint_nanny_calibrate">
        </div>
    </div>

</div>
